humanMachineDialogue.text: The report mentions 'Metastases carcinomatosae in lymphonodis axillae (No XIX/XXI)', which means that cancer metastases were found in 19 out of 21 assessed axillary lymph nodes. According to the new rule 13, N3 indicates metastases in 4 or more axillary lymph nodes, which is satisfied in this case. Therefore, the N stage for this patient's cancer is N3.
